Program: Outlook
Title: 26/07/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00vqn3z
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 27 Jul 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, supermodel Alek Wek tells us about returning to her homeland South Sudan as a UN refugee envoy, and remembers how war affected her own life. Also, the last traditional mussel fishermen of Portonovo in Italy. They dive on a local reef for wild mussels, but say young people would rather sunbathe or swim, and the tradition is dying out. Show less